SERVERS

(1) A computer that listens for incoming requests from the clients (frontend).
(2) For example, Apache Ngins, IIS servers, Tomcat

TYPES OF SERVERS

(1) STATIC: 
(i) A static web server or stack consists of a computer (hardware) with an HTTP server (software).
(ii) We call it “static” because the server sends its hosted files as it is to your browser”.
(iii) It response/server static content.

(2) DYNAMIC:
(i) A dynamic web server consists of a static web server plus extra software, most commonly an application server and a database.
(ii) “dynamic” because the application server updates the hosted files before sending them to your browser visa the HTTP server.
(iii) Dynamic Server responses/serves dynamic contents.

